    "description": "Compare README-level and source-level descriptions for Screenpipe MCP local activity tools.",
    "instruction_variants": [
      {
        "instructions": "Choose the single Screenpipe MCP tool that should be called next. Broad time-range questions about what the user did should start with activity-summary. Specific keyword or exact phrase lookup should use keyword-search. Specific text, transcript lines, screen text, speaker/window filtering, tags, or memories should use search-content. UI controls, buttons, links, fields, or page structure should use search-elements. Full context for a known frame should use frame-context. Specific frame UI elements should use get-frame-elements. Meeting inventory should use list-meetings; a known meeting id should use get-meeting; editing a meeting note should use update-meeting only after preserving existing notes. Scheduled automation creation should use create-pipe only after reading the pipes guide in a resource-capable host; in this tool-only matrix choose create-pipe for the creation step. After create/edit, run-pipe tests and pipe-logs verifies.",
        "name": "screenpipe_host_rules"
      }
    ],
